{
  "text": "The global threshold applicable when the intensity distribution of objects and background pixels are sufficiently distinct. In the global threshold, a single threshold value is used in the whole image. The global threshold has been a popular technique in many years [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . When the pixel values of the components and that of background are fairly consistent in their respective values over the entire image, global thresholding could be used.",
